cs.DL, cs.SI, cs.IR, cs.CY, cs.CR

The paper discusses the relationship between various metrics of scientific publications, including article views and citations, which are relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. cs.DL (Digital Libraries) is the most likely sub-category as it deals with the management and dissemination of digital information, including scholarly publications. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) are also likely as they involve the analysis of social attention and metrics related to scholarly publications. cs.CY (Cryptography and Security) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) are less likely but still possible as they may involve the analysis of metrics related to the impact and dissemination of research in these fields.
